<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Degree-course-on-biotech-and-biosafety-launched-at-Kenya-s-Moi-University" title="Degree course on biotech and biosafety launched at Kenya's Moi University " alt="link">Degree course on biotech and biosafety launched at Kenya's Moi University </a></h2>

	
					<p>








 




  
  

	
	<a href="/var/knowledge/storage/images/media/images/logos/kenya-moi-university-2/285727-1-eng-GB/kenya-moi-university-2.jpg" rel="lightbox[]">	
	  </a>
	
		
			
	
  	






	 
  





	A degree course in biotechnology and biosafety was launched at Moi University in Kenya School of Science, Department of Biological Sciences (DBS) on September 11, 2009. The new degree program was developed by Dr. Donald F. Otieno and other colleagues in the DBS with support from the Program for Biosafety Systems (PBS). Contributions were also made by PBS partners at Michigan State University's Institute of International Agriculture. Through course work, seminars, field and laboratory training, this new degree program will provide students with a comprehensive understanding of the principles and practices of biotechnology and biosafety as well as biosafety regulatory processes and how these can be implemented and properly enforced to support agricultural and biotechnological innovations. (Source: ISAAA, date unknown)</p>
							<p><span class="date">20/10/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Degree-course-on-biotech-and-biosafety-launched-at-Kenya-s-Moi-University">Read more...</a>
