<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Selection-of-sub-regional-focal-institutions-for-AFAFE" title="Selection of sub-regional focal institutions for AFAFE" alt="document">Selection of sub-regional focal institutions for AFAFE</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>Created in 1993, the African Network for Education in Agriculture, Agroforestry and Natural Resource Management (ANAFE) includes 131 universities and Agricultural Colleges in 35 African countries and aims to improve the quality, relevance and the application of higher agricultural education in Africa. From January 2010, the Regional Forums for Agricultural Education (RAFTs) will be supported by institutions focal selected from member institutions in each region who will appoint Senior Education Fellow (SEF) within them. Deadline for applications: October 30, 2009. See the document attached for more details. </p>
