<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Final-Communique-of-40th-Pacific-Islands-Forum-Cairns-Australia" title="Final Communiqué of 40th Pacific Islands Forum, Cairns, Australia" alt="link">Final Communiqué of 40th Pacific Islands Forum, Cairns, Australia</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Fortieth Pacific Islands Forum was held in Cairns, Australia from 5 to 6 August 2009 and was attended by Heads of State and Governments of Australia, the Cook Islands, Federated States of Micronesia, the Republic of Nauru, New Zealand, Niue, Papua New Guinea, the Republic of the Marshall Islands, Samoa, Solomon Islands, Tonga, Tuvalu and the Republic of Vanuatu. New Caledonia and French Polynesia attended the formal session as associate members. Timor-Leste, Tokelau, Wallis and Futuna, the Asian Development Bank, the Commonwealth Secretariat, the United Nations and the Western and Central Pacific Fisheries Commission attended as observers. Topics such as pacific maritime safety, climate change, renewable energy and others are discussed. The outcome of this meeting is provided on the website of Pacific Islands Forum Secretariat.</p>
							<p><span class="date">25/09/2009</span></p>
