						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CTA-Update-on-TEEAL" title="CTA Update on TEEAL" alt="document">CTA Update on TEEAL</a></h2>

	
	
	
	
					<p>CTA <b>extends the deadline</b> for accepting applications to assist universities and research institutions in qualifying African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) countries in their initial purchase of “The Essential Electronic Agricultural Library” (TEEAL) in the Local Area Networked (LAN) version. The initial subscription includes the complete contents of 149 journals published over a 17 year period from 1993 to 2009. TEEAL has a total value of over US$1 million for these 17 years of information, but an initial subscription costs US$5,000. Annual updates are provided a year after the date of publication. Thus, the 2008 update will be available at the end of 2009 and the 2009 update will be available at the end of 2010. CTA is willing to assist with the initial investment (1993-2009) to improve library resources for the furtherance of agricultural research in the ACP region. In return ACP institutions must undertake to sign TEEAL’s licensing agreement and pay for annual updates from 2010 onwards. The 2010 update will cost US$ 525. Prices for 2011 will be confirmed at a later date. You can download the application form in English here.</p>
							<p><span class="date">18/09/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="document" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/CTA-Update-on-TEEAL">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
